definition: to possess/to have/equipped with/able to fulfill (conditions or requirements)
tool/device/utensil/equipment/instrument/talent/ability/to possess/to have/to provide/to furnish/to state/classifier for devices, coffins, dead bodies
to prepare/get ready/to provide or equip

sentences.english: Moreover, the skull has features resembling those of contemporary Asians.
sentences.chinese: 此外，該頭骨具備類似現代亞洲人頭骨的特徵。

sentences.english: Compared with utterance understanding, pragmatic presupposition has the basic features of appropriateness and common acceptance.
sentences.chinese: 相對於話語理解，語用預設具備合適性和共知性。

sentences.english: Commodity money takes the form of a commodity with intrinsic value.
sentences.chinese: 貨幣本身即具備某種固有財貨的價值。

sentences.english: The bursts have much more energy than the normal local variations in temperature.
sentences.chinese: 這樣的爆發具備相比常規溫變強大的多的能量。

sentences.english: The key account manager must possess significant skill to run a multi-million dollar business.
sentences.chinese: 大客戶經理須具備經營數百萬美元生意的重要技能。

sentences.english: A privately-run school shall have the qualifications of a legal person.
sentences.chinese: 民辦學校應當具備法人條件。

sentences.english: I hope my future prince charming has such a personality.
sentences.chinese: 我希望自己未來的白馬王子也具備這樣的個性。

sentences.english: They are related in many ways and need to be managed in a holistic approach.
sentences.chinese: 她們之間在品牌辦理的好些個方面上具備接洽瓜葛性。

sentences.english: So you don't have ductility, which is what you have in metal.
sentences.chinese: 所以材料不具備延展性，而且金屬中有自由電子。

sentences.english: Objective To study the clinical features of central scotoma in glaucoma.
sentences.chinese: 目的探討發生於青光眼的中央暗點所具備的臨牀特徵。

sentences.english: There was already more than enough femininity in his life.
sentences.chinese: 他的生命已經具備了夠充足的女性成份。

sentences.english: The State Department is simply not equipped to handle interdepartmental machinery.
sentences.chinese: 國務院根本不具備駕馭部際機構的能力。

sentences.english: Foot switch board has quick lowering function when unload.
sentences.chinese: 腳踏開關板具備空載快速下降功能。

sentences.english: Fetus already have hearing now and you can begin a prenatal education.
sentences.chinese: 胎兒已具備聽力，能聽見聲音，可開始進行胎教了。

sentences.english: He had many elegancies of his own, whilst he scoffed at conventional elegance.
sentences.chinese: 他本人便具備很多優雅，儘管他在譏笑常規的優雅。

sentences.english: The Nominees must have at least 1year continuous full-time service with the organization.
sentences.chinese: 被提名者必須具備持續至少一年在該部門服務的經歷。
